Japan supports Russia's participation in political  talks of a summit to be held by the Group of Seven (G7) industrialised  countries from July 8-10 in Naples, official sources said on Monday.
Dominant opinions at a G7 summit preparatory meeting held earlier this  month in Italy supported Russia's participation in the political discussions,  news reports said.
Japan is consulting with other G7 members on whether Russia should be  allowed to attend economic talks at the Naples summit, government sources said.
News reports quoted Japan's vice foreign minister Kunihiko Saito as saying  here on Monday that it was too early for Russia to attend G7 economic talks.
The G7 groups Britain, Canada, France, Germany, Italy, Japan and the  United States. It issues economic and political statements at the end of its  annual summit.
